The oldest known Cenozoic species of Chrysopidae is Sinonothochrysa zhangi Huang et Nel in
Huang et al. (2021)
from the Paleocene of southern China (
Huang et al. 2021
). Its venation is characteristic of the subfamily Nothochrysinae (see its diagnosis of Makarkin & Archibald 2013 ), including the long Sc, the short intramedian cell, and the proximal position of the crossvein 2m-cu. It is interesting that the hind wing MA in this oldest Nothochrysinae is apomorphic, fused for some distance with RP as in most other genera of the subfamily.

